        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 31 at 4:38PM MDT until July 31 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Cuchara Pass,
or 30 miles west of Trinidad, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Spanish Peaks, Cuchara, Cuchara Pass, Indian Creek on the
southeastern Spring Burn Scar, Spring Burn Scar south of Highway 160
in Huerfano county, and southeastern Spring Burn Scar south of
Highway 160 in Costilla county.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
